{
  "image": "6542\\6542.jpg",
  "title": "Connor's Gonna Tell: The Táin Bó Cúailnge",
  "description": "It’s the Táin Bó Cúailnge! From Old Irish: Táin (raid), Bó (cattle), Cúailnge (the name of really big cow). We’re going to steal him! There are many táins, but this one stars Cúchulainn, the most murdery boy-hero of Ireland. Winner of the 2022 Redlocks Award at the MN Fringe. Epic story telling punctuated by comic dramaturgy.",
  "credits": "<strong>Director</strong>: Alexander Gerchak<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Connor M. McEvoy Bradley Kallhoff<br/>",
  "website": "https://instagram.com/thehazelruse",
  "plain_language": "A fast, funny take on an ancient Irish story! When a powerful queen tries to steal a legendary bull, only a teenage hero named Cúchulainn, immune to a strange curse, can stop her army. This fast-baced show is packed with battles, myths, big emotions, and even bigger cows.",
